Class PublicFieldParser

  • Object
    • PublicFieldParser

  • public class PublicFieldParser
extends Object
    PublicFieldParser defines a parser to recognize a descriptor of a field in a string, and return an object representing the sort of field it is in the corresponding class. The descriptor is expected to be in the form : where the is a fully qualified name of the form ... The parser first checks that the descriptor is in the right syntactic form, then extracts the type and field-name and uses reflection to determine if the field belongs to the class, and the types match.
